         <div type="transcription">
            <p>
<lb corresp="#a1"/><gap reason="lost"/><w>śilacandre</w><w>porocineṃ</w><w>pissaṅk</w>
<lb corresp="#a2"/><gap reason="lost"/><w><supplied>ka</supplied>pyārac</w><w>wram</w><w>prakseñci</w><w>ku</w>
<lb corresp="#a3"/><gap reason="lost"/><gap reason="plain" quantity="1"/><w>r</w><w>puk</w><w>salu</w><w>paṣ</w><seg type="monogram">¤</seg>
<lb corresp="#a4"/><gap reason="lost"/><w><supplied>wiki</supplied>-ñupyaṃ</w><w>watku</w><seg type="monogram">¤</seg></p>
         </div>
         <div type="translation">
            <p><choice corresp="#a1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... Śīlacandra ... the monastery of Porociṃ</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... they ask of you the thing for a <hi>kapyār</hi></seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... give all completely! ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a4"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... order of the 29th ... [Signum] </seg></seg></choice></p>
         </div>
         <div type="comments">
            <p><note type="philcomment">Edition and translation based on <bibl><title corresp="ref:ogihara2014"/><citedRange>112</citedRange></bibl> with corrections by Ilya Itkin (p.c.).</note><note corresp="#a3" type="philcomment"><hi>salu paṣ</hi>: This reading, instead of <hi>salapaṣ</hi> (<bibl><title corresp="ref:ogihara2014"/><citedRange>112</citedRange></bibl>), follows <bibl><title corresp="ref:carlingetal2009"/><citedRange>42a</citedRange></bibl> (Sergey Malyshev and Ilya Itkin, p.c.).</note><note corresp="#a4" type="philcomment"><hi>(wiki)-ñupyaṃ</hi>: Literally, 'on the 29': <hi>(wiki)-ñupyaṃ</hi> is the loc. of <hi>wiki-ñupi</hi> '29', denoting the date of the order (cf. also <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-tht1519"/> 3). This restoration follows a suggestion of Ilya Itkin (p.c.). An alternative restoration would be <hi>(śäk)-ñupyaṃ</hi>, in which case there was a virāma after <hi>(śäk)</hi>, i.e. <distinct type="ms_text">(_ś_a_k\)-ñupya[ṃ]</distinct>.</note></p>
         </div>
         <div type="bibliography">
            <p><label>Online access</label><bibl><title corresp="ref:idp0000"/><ref target="http://idp.bbaw.de/database/oo_loader.a4d?pm=THT 4023" type="external">THT 4023</ref></bibl><bibl><title corresp="ref:tht0000">TITUS</title><ref target="http://titus.fkidg1.uni-frankfurt.de/texte/tocharic/tht/40/4023.htm" type="external">THT 4023</ref></bibl>. </p>
            <p><label>Edition</label><bibl><title corresp="ref:tamai2007a"/><citedRange>№4023</citedRange></bibl>; <bibl><title corresp="ref:ogihara2014"/><citedRange>112-113</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
         </div>
